reviews: A great headlamp, consistent with the quality and performance expected from fenix. Significant improvement over earlier dual lamp models. BUT the use of magnesium rather than aluminum for the body is a poor choice. The magnesium is so soft that the body has been significantly dinged and chipped from inadvertent drops onto concrete from no more than 12". While the damage is of course cosmetic, it probably would not be encountered with a traditional aluminum body. Still highly recommended, but disappointing that such an expensive light, intended for rugged use, is so easily dinged up.

reviews:
I mostly see other cavers using zebralights. I did try a zebralight but I wanted something brighter with longer burn times so I returned it. I bought the Fenix HM65R after reading the manufacturer claims about lumens and burn time. I actually thought that there is no way this headlamp is as efficient as they're claiming. Well, it is. I can go into a cave for 6 or so hours on a medium setting and have plenty of light. When im done and check the battery indicator it shows the battery is still 3/4 full. Amazing. They boast it will last 20 hours on high. I've not tried that because it hasn't been necessary. The medium setting is more than bright enough for navigating a cave. Honestly the burn time alone sold me on this headlamp but some other great features are that you can charge it with a usb cable, it has both a flood and spot light, its relatively light and very easy to use.

Update: I found one con. It doesn't take standard 18650 batteries. The battery that it comes with is great though but dont think you can bring a standard 18650 as a spare in case the battery dies

review_title: Great addition to the Fenix family. Great Headlamp!
reviews:
This Fenix light (like all their lights) is awesome. I also have the HM50R that I love but the smaller battery just needed charged to often. I do appliance repair and keep my headlight in a zipper case in my side pocket and use it several times a day. HM65R is great. Very light weight even with the 18650 battery. I removed the over-the-head strap and with the Fenix non-slip coating on the inside of the headband it wears very well. Never slips down on my forehead.
The USB C charging is a great plus too. Phone, ear buds, and now head lamp use same cable.
Referring to the "hood" above the power buttons: not an issue. Does not interfere with powering on the light.
The four light battery meter is a great plus too for quickly tapping either power button to check battery level.

Update 7-1-20: The hood over the power buttons is a GREAT idea. The hood keeps the light form accidentally being powered on when not in use. I found a perfect size zipper case for this headlamp. https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07J41LFJH/ref=cm_sw_em_r_mt_dp_U_PCv.Eb3JHY381
Still highly recommend this headlamp.

review_title: Now THIS is a bright headlamp!
reviews: Both the wide angle and the spot beams are fantastic. Very bright at the highest settings and great battery life when dimmed. The color temperature is on the warm side rather than a more bluish light. Color rendering is just OK but that is not really what this light is all about. The band adjustment might be tight is you have a big head. I have mine set nearly all the way out and my head is average. Compared to any of the other such lights I have tried, this is hands down the brightest.
